Browser Extensions Security Review

Repository Description

This repository documents the review and analysis of browser extensions installed on Google Chrome and Opera browsers. The objective of this task is to identify installed extensions, evaluate their permissions, determine whether any extensions are malicious or suspicious, and document actions taken to improve browser security and performance.


---

Objective

To review all installed browser extensions

To identify unused or suspicious extensions

To understand the risks of malicious browser extensions

To document actions taken and final security status



---

Tools Used

Google Chrome Browser

Opera Browser

Built-in Extensions Manager



---

Browser 1: Google Chrome

Extensions Identified

1. Google Docs Offline

Purpose: Allows users to create, edit, and view Google Docs, Sheets, and Slides without an internet connection.

Permissions: Access limited to Google Docs services.

Security Status: Safe and trusted (official Google extension).

Action Taken: Kept (useful and non-malicious).


2. Microsoft Bing Search for Chrome

Purpose: Sets Microsoft Bing as the default search engine in Chrome.

Permissions: Modifies search provider settings.

Security Status: Safe but optional.

Action Taken: Can be removed if not required.

---

Browser 2: Opera

Extensions Identified

1. Opera Ad Blocker

Purpose: Blocks advertisements and trackers to improve browsing speed and privacy.

Permissions: Access to web content for ad blocking.

Security Status: Safe (official Opera extension).

Action Taken: Kept (recommended).


2. Opera Wallet

Purpose: Cryptocurrency wallet integration in Opera browser.

Permissions: Used only for crypto-related activities.

Security Status: Safe but optional.

Action Taken: Disabled if not in use.



---

Performance Check

Browser restarted after review

No suspicious behavior observed

Normal browsing speed and reduced ads (Opera)



---

Research: How Malicious Extensions Harm Users

Malicious browser extensions can:

Steal passwords and personal data

Track browsing activity

Inject unwanted advertisements

Redirect users to malicious websites

Slow down system performance



---

Final Summary

Total extensions reviewed: 4

Malicious extensions found: None

Suspicious extensions: None

Overall browser security status: Safe



---

Conclusion

All installed extensions in both Google Chrome and Opera browsers are legitimate and safe. No malicious extensions were detected during the review.


